title: The top 10 songs and albums on the iTunes Store
text:
Home » News » Entertainment » Music » The top 10 songs… The top 10 songs and albums on the iTunes Store By The Associated Press October 16, 2015 11:35 am 
iTunes’ Official Music Charts for the week ending Oct. 15, 2015: 
Top Songs 
2. The Hills, The Weeknd 
3. Wildest Dreams, Taylor Swift 
4. Stitches, Shawn Mendes 
5. Same Old Love, Selena Gomez 
6. What Do You Mean?, Justin Bieber 
7. Locked Away (feat. Adam Levine), R. City 
8. Downtown (feat. Eric Nally, Me., Macklemore & Ryan Lewis 
9. The Hills (feat. Eminem), The Weeknd 
10. Ex’s & Oh’s, Elle King 
Top Albums 
1. The Documentary 2, The Game 
2. Revival, Selena Gomez 
3. Beauty Behind the Madness, The Weeknd 
4. What a Time To Be Alive, Drake & Future 
5. Purpose (Deluxe), Justin Bieber 
6. 1989, Taylor Swift 
7. Made In The A.M., One Direction 
8. NOW That’s What I Call Music, ., Various Artists 
9. The Incredible True Story, Logic 
10. Fetty Wap, Fetty Wap
